  "texts": [
    "To maintain efficiency and real-world applicability, we opt for a sparse retriever.",
    "In the natural language question perturbation, both SFT CodeS-7B and SFT CodeS-15B outperform the previous best, Chat-GPT + ZeroNL2SQL, scoring 74.3% and 75.2% versus 73.2%.",
    "This suggests our models have a better of question semantics, leading to more accurate SQL queries.",
    "For SQL perturbations, our models slightly lag behind RESDSQL-3B + NatSQL.",
    "The latter's intermediary SQL representation, NatSQL, is more simple than SQL and aids its performance."
  ],
